{"_id":"xycnwa7UDvYmERl2","name":"Table of Contents","content":"<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[kP1dpSNXZQQZl2dT]{Cover}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[huAupV3vSEvjCR8x]{Credits}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[25PGxOJU0npmyASD]{Introduction}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[VhDI2Ow3vTdP0Mn4]{Adventure Flowchart}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[hV3m7EUbOWIqXjOt]{The Plague}</p>\n<h2>Episode 1</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[8NxhL4G6P6VZWecV]{Ep1: Scene A}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[bQaZB7SLNBIbVOlt]{Ep1: Scene B}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[Yf87YqXwb2GKKqhI]{Ep1: Scene C}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[FCfvZbX6Hea1eEsE]{Ep1: Scene D}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Episode 2</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[TH6qXLMxW2InVRSL]{Ep2: Scene A}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[4wKJz2RhtqZhdBGM]{Ep2: Scene B}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[scxCOCEnQLMZVtZ8]{Ep2: Scene C}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[eeoVrkjdOdUQ7mM8]{Ep2: Scene D}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[xUCLwKJ25VfOYrKo]{Ep2: Scene E}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[YmnXtPcC9BeysJek]{Ep2: Playing the Pillars}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Episode 3</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[VRys3CAaI2DQpIxF]{Ep3: Scene A}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[FkuPbvyb2Ik68N9c]{Ep3: Scene B}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[EvoLeaBo6NN08IkU]{Ep3: Scene C}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[3sX7RApiUecVlpaV]{Ep3: Scene D}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[yU1tZLABSUMgxCeQ]{Ep3: Playing the Pillars}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Conclusion</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[rKEBsHeQbxmvvz97]{Wrap-up}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[PTWZJS8Pe5dTuOvy]{Adventure Rewards}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Bonus Objective A</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[faJOPkfyracQTR9R]{BO-A: Scene A}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[vcW76za3Lf5A76HE]{BO-A: Scene B}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[R6EkJGlMMcBz8OqT]{BO-A: Playing the Pillars}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Bonus Objective B</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[bKtCuoOUIN9LNr8s]{BO-B: Scene A}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[jgzQMC6MkYm77IhP]{BO-B: Scene B}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[p2CfgBp8vs3eOMBz]{BO-B: Playing the Pillars}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Locations and NPCs</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[eaxc8JJnxv9UeLdS]{Locations &amp; NPCs}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Story Awards</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[7ld34ihq4j4xrXQ3]{B&amp;E}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[iGRPLBSQLPMet0wp]{Tinder Hearts}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Magic Item Reward</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[BtN7daM04mE7s8O8]{Magic Item}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Handouts</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[FjudcX5bBqDt6D4Y]{Player Handout 1}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[qoCbcHlc2taSgfe3]{Player Handout 2}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[MxGV1xkZQ6boo5gM]{Player Handout 3}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[5mSBhU6WVXcahjJ1]{Player Handout 4}</p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">DM Tips</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[pDywPrqqFwuONrXv]{Dungeon Master Tips}</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.KfZAQDC8Tx8Bhn20","hash":"06cc679522024732f7c7964505188889e56c1b3a"},"cf":{"id":"temp_m0p47tcdiqi","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Begin Here","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"GEigN7tJTpcsIngx","name":"Adventure Flowchart","content":"<h1><span style=\"font-size:20.0pt;font-family:'Andada SC';mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Episode Flowchart</span></h1>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">This section provides a basic understanding of not only the flow of the episode, but also the outline of the different paths that your players may take in reaching their stated objective.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\"> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/pla01-tmacm/assetts/Flowchart.webp\" width=\"568\" height=\"424\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.VhDI2Ow3vTdP0Mn4","hash":"553243bea007dc99eee62537aec45f51fe284745"},"cf":{"id":"temp_m0p47tcdiqi","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Begin Here","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"SrP3BpnCIa3KvWzc","name":"Adventure Rewards","content":"<div class=\"WordSection1\">\n<h1><span style=\"font-size:20.0pt;font-family:'Andada SC';mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Adventure Rewards</span></h1>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">See ALPG <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">(</span><span class=\"ItalicSerif\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Adventurers League Player</span><span class=\"ItalicSerif\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">’s Guide)</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"> for advancement rewards.</span></p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Player Rewards</h2>\n</div>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">The characters earn the following player rewards for <span class=\"BoldSerif\">completing the adventure</span>:</p>\n<h3>Magic Item Unlock</h3>\n<p>Characters completing the adventure unlock:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\"> <em><strong>   </strong></em></span><em><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Gloves of Climbing and Swimming.</span></strong></em> The rust colored Gloves of Chakalakhan are constructed of articulated boiled leather. <span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\"> </span>While wearing these when you strike an enemy you hear faint fragments of the ancient battle song of the great hobgoblin war chief Chakalakhan.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\">This item can be found in the @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.SvQn5t0M8ALcq7eV]{Magic Item Reward}</p>\n<h3>Story Awards</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">Characters playing the adventure may earn:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>B&amp;E.</span> </strong>You entered the Manor without securing permission from Constable Hobb and have been arrested for breaking and entering.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\">More information can be found in @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.u0aqhnLQdM79zmkm]{B&amp;E}</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"> <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Tinder Hearts.</span></strong> You have put the ghost of Renny Tinderhobb to rest by reuniting him and his kobold doll. More information can be found in @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.9pasI5abhzmDRZEm]{Tinder Hearts}.</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Dungeon Master Rewards</h2>\n</div>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark:_Hlk518324581\">See the ALDMG (<span class=\"ItalicSerif\">Adventurers League </span>Dungeon<span class=\"ItalicSerif\"> Master’s Guide</span>) for more information about DM Quests.</span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"> </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.PTWZJS8Pe5dTuOvy","hash":"4f15db87b7f935f84e7d9f3463a7921bf0b8d6cc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_javh7op4th","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Conclusion","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"u0aqhnLQdM79zmkm","name":"B&E","content":"<div class=\"WordSection1\">\n<h1><span style=\"font-size:20.0pt;font-family:'Andada SC';mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Appendix 11: Story Rewards (Player Handout 5)</span></h1>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language:EN-US\"> </span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\">During the course of this adventure, the characters may earn the following story award. If you are printing these out for your characters, print as many as you may need to ensure that any eligible character receives a copy:</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:'ヒラギノ角ゴ Pro W3';color:black;mso-fareast-language:JA\"> </span></p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>B&amp;E</h2>\n</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">You have entered the Manor without securing permission from Constable Hobb and have been arrested for breaking and entering. You spend a day in lockup and do some minor community service before being released from the constable’s charge.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\">Glister law enforcement will be wary of your activities in town until you can prove yourself. <br />Hobb will require some additional task in the future to clear your name completely.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"> <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Removed this story award upon completion of Part 2 of the Plaguestone trilogy: A Mine of Their Own.</span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"> </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.7ld34ihq4j4xrXQ3","hash":"2de9feb0446984e22a3ee21124626d17abb771e7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qexw51e44oh","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Story Rewards","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"3gprDTt1rFpzC63c","name":"BO-A: Playing the Pillars","content":"<h2 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light', sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">Playing the Pillars</span></h2>\n<h3 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light', sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">Combat</span></h3>\n<p class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\">The cultists are not as into all of this as the cult fanatics. The cultists will surrender or run away if dropped to half their hit points. Cult fanatics will fight to the death. </p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light',sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:#9b3737;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span></p>\n<h3 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light', sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">Exploration</span></h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">At the cemetery if the party approaches the misty graves without trying to be stealthy they may end up being surprised. </p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span></p>\n<h3 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light',sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">SOCIAL</span></h3>\n<p class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\">It is possible to infiltrate the cult itself by convincing one of the cult fanatics or an acolyte that you are there to join. DC 20 Charisma (deception) check to trick them. The players may also try persuading them or intimidating them depending on the situation. </p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt\"> </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"3c170f678b330d115e4f7aae86ba5d497cb4d2c3","sourceId":"JournalEntry.R6EkJGlMMcBz8OqT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_avljyl6g1mj","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Bonus Objective A","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"J4cUImPGj7IiXdi2","name":"BO-A: Scene A","content":"<div class=\"WordSection1\">\n<h1><span style=\"font-size:20.0pt;font-family:'Andada SC';mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Appendix 5: Pyre Liar (Bonus Objective A.)</span></h1>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\"><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Estimated Duration:</span> 60 minutes</p>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Cambria',serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:'ヒラギノ角ゴ Pro W3';mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:JA;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span></p>\n<div class=\"WordSection2\">\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Setting Description</h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Cambria',serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:'ヒラギノ角ゴ Pro W3';mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:JA;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\">South of the road into Glister behind a hillock constable Hobb has set aside an area to burn the bodies of the deceased from the plague.</p>\n<h3>Prerequisites</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">The players can arrive from <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Episode 1 scene @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.XtNfsRzPiMkSac0B]{A}, @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.ePDLStr72jYy9l9F]{B}, or @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.fMnWcVYtGAr6KrWh]{C}</strong> It is also possible to arrive here at a later stage in the investigation, time permitting.</p>\n<h3>Area Information</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">This area features:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>Dimensions &amp; Terrain. </span></strong>The small hillock conceals the burning pyres from the town gate and main road into Glister. A muddy cart track leads around the hill to an area filled with thick smoke.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>Lighting.</span></strong> The smoke keeps the area <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">lightly obscured</em>.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>Smell.</span> </strong>The smell of burning thatch and cord wood fill the air.</p>\n<h3>Objectives</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">The players need to determine that the bodies are not being burned at the pyres and witness the cult’s activities at midnight in the graveyard.</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Scene A. Smoke and Mires</h2>\n</div>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt\">\n<p class=\"BoxedText\">Following the path around a small hill you see the source of the smoke, a large pyre of almost bond fire proportions burns with two attendants feeding the flames with an occasional log.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">  </span>Your eyes sting from the smoke as it wafts around the area. A lone mule munches greedily on a pile of hay that sits next to stacks of cord wood besides a tarp covered cart.</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Creatures/NPCs</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">A @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.vZ9oEp3vNt4ghIFp]{Cultist} and a @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.p66xHrKbVux9M8eA]{Cult Fanatic} are tending to a large bier upon which a great smoking fire is burning.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\">A successful <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">DC 12</strong> Wisdom (Perception) Check, made at disadvantage due to the smoke, will reveal that there are no bodies in pyre, but plenty of hay and wood.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Objectives/Goals.</span></strong> They have been smuggling bodies from the tent hospital in the cart when they go through the town gate during shift change. Carting them up to their lair under Coppertop Manor in the dead of night. None of them have been burned. Only wood and hay are being burned to create the smoke. To avoid suspicion the cultist try to steer the party towards Daeomer or Hobb, suggesting that they have something to hide.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">What Do They Know?</span> </strong>If questioned the attendants will reveal:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>The lack of bodies is because they are waiting for the next delivery of deceased from the tent hospital (False)</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>They kept the pyres burning for the last three days, it’s easier than restarting it each time. (Partially true)</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>They work in 8-hour shifts, two at a time (True)</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Constable Hobb ordered the pyres after he discovered that bodies had been going missing at the cemetery. (True)</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Daeomer runs the cemetery, he didn’t want anyone to know graves had been disturbed. (Mostly True)</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>They work for Ginna (Truer than you know)</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>If “convinced” by the players with a DC 20 Charisma check the cult fanatic will reveal that they have a ritual planned for midnight at the cemetery. (True)</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\"> </p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid #F2F2F2 1.5pt;mso-border-themecolor:background1;mso-border-themeshade:242;padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\">\n<h3 class=\"SidebarHeading\">Adjusting the Scene<span class=\"MsoCommentReference\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-fareast-language:EN-US\"> </span></span></h3>\n<p class=\"SidebarBody\">Here are some suggestions for adjusting this scene, according to your group.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span class=\"BoldSerif\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Very Weak: </span>Replace the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cult fanatic</strong> with a <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cultist</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span class=\"BoldSerif\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Weak: </span>Remove the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cultist</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Strong: </span>Remove the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cultist</strong> add one <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cult fanatic</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Very Strong: </span>Add one <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cult fanatic</strong> and one<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> cultist</strong>.</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Treasure &amp; Rewards</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">Each cult fanatic carries a @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.items.I4ChTaMzp0Zi9Qlw]{Bone Skull Mask}. The players will also find a piece of parchment with a note scratched into it <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">See </strong>@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.ZLaOBZ2vtLUMY4TQ]{Player Handout 4}.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulleted\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Monetary Treasure.</span> @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.items.I4ChTaMzp0Zi9Qlw]{Bone Skull Masks} </strong>are art objects that are worth 5gp each if a player wishes to keep one.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">  </span></p>\n<hr />\n<p class=\"CoreBulleted\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\">See @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.3gprDTt1rFpzC63c]{BO-A: Playing the Pillars} for more info.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.faJOPkfyracQTR9R","hash":"2d89852fecb77c84f3e22c8af6384f4bb55035f5"},"cf":{"id":"temp_avljyl6g1mj","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Bonus Objective A","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"qD0nBCdoiNARkjnz","name":"BO-A: Scene B","content":"<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Scene B. Rise</h2>\n</div>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">Following the lead given by the cult fanatic in <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Scene A </strong>or if the players wish to stake out the graveyard overnight hey will encounter visitors at midnight.</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt\">\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"BoxedText\">As an eerie fog descends from the hilltop, glowing headstones peak above the sea of mist in the moonlight like a flotilla of the lost. The mists and dim shadows seem to converge on a set of graves...</p>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n<h3>Area Information</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">This area features:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>Dimensions &amp; Terrain. </span>The ground is soft and grassy keeping sounds muffled.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Lighting.</span> The mist and moonlight keep the area <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">lightly obscured</em>.</p>\n<h3>Creatures/NPCs</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">An @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.Kj5CzFhjjCpX8ECX]{Acolyte} and 4 @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.vZ9oEp3vNt4ghIFp]{Cultists} sneak into the graveyard. Roll a group stealth check for them with advantage due to the dim light and the mist to see if they go unnoticed by the party.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Objectives/Goals.</span></strong> The cultists are here to raise some zombies as practice and tribute to Thang’ard their cultist obsession. The zombies will be useful to the cult and can later be shipped to Thang’ard’s lair in Thar.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>If the cultists are not immediately discovered and confronted they manage to raise 4 <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">zombies</strong> before combat starts, otherwise the zombies will rise in the second round of combat and join the fray.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">What Do They Know?</span> </strong>If captured or confronted the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Acolyte</strong> will enlighten the party:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>They must get back to the inner sanctum or “she” will be angry.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Thang’ard is bringing death to the living and life to the dead with a relic of great suffering.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Glister is just a test of the true power of Thang’ard</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\"> </p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid #F2F2F2 1.5pt;mso-border-themecolor:background1;mso-border-themeshade:242;padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\">\n<p class=\"SidebarHeading\">Adjusting the Scene<span class=\"MsoCommentReference\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-fareast-language:EN-US\"> </span></span></p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBody\">Here are some suggestions for adjusting this scene, according to your group.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span class=\"BoldSerif\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Very Weak: </span>Remove the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">acolyte,</strong> two <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cultists </strong>and<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> </strong>three<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> zombies</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span class=\"BoldSerif\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Weak: </span>Remove the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">acolyte</strong> and one <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cultist</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Strong: </span>Replace the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">acolyte</strong> with a @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.p66xHrKbVux9M8eA]{Cult Fanatic} remove one <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">zombie</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Very Strong: </span>Add one <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">cult fanatic</strong> and one<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> acolyte</strong>.</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Treasure &amp; Rewards</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">One of the cultists will be carrying the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">medallion</strong> displayed in @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.pGjavBU1kA94Vc7z]{Player Handout 2}<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> </strong>It is six inches in diameter made of bronze and copper. Also, each cult fanatic, if present, carries a <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">bone skull mask</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><em><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Monetary Treasure.</span> </strong></em>The cultist <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">medallion </strong>is an art object that is worth 10gp if a player wishes to keep it.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">  </span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Bone skull masks</strong> are art objects that are worth 5gp each if a player wishes to keep one.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\"> </span></p>\n<hr />\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt\">See @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.3gprDTt1rFpzC63c]{BO-A: Playing the Pillars} for more info.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.vcW76za3Lf5A76HE","hash":"94ac2695f2a6872670c3ff44c0c166de76e52399"},"cf":{"id":"temp_avljyl6g1mj","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Bonus Objective A","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"UJCAwvjiBXBd2sOC","name":"BO-B: Playing the Pillars","content":"<div class=\"WordSection1\">\n<h2 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light', sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">Playing the Pillars</span></h2>\n<h3 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light', sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">Combat</span></h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"WordSection2\">\n<p class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\">The players can put Renny Tinderhobb to rest by destroying his ghost. If the players take this option, the@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.PZ7ZY9XYevBdyevq]{Swarms of Rats} from @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.Sc8jn8Ht7NNQSbkx]{BO-B: Scene B}<strong>. </strong>come out of the walls and join the fight.</p>\n<span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light',sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:#9b3737;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"><br /></span>\n<h3 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light', sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">Exploration</span></h3>\n<p class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\">While exploring the manor the players may encounter hazards as described in the DMG pg. 105.</p>\n<p class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\">Feel free to add additional pit falls as necessary to keep the tension up.</p>\n<span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light',sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:#9b3737;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"><br /></span>\n<h3 class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\"><span style=\"font-family:'Copperplate Gothic Light',sans-serif;color:#9b3737\">SOCIAL</span></h3>\n<p class=\"PlayingthePillarsBody\">Talking with Renny Tinderhobb will reveal that he was a curious and rambunctious boy. The cultists have had one run-in with him and decided it was best to leave him alone. His presence keeps lookie-loos away and Gina has more important things to worry about.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"4b5b442df2cc76b464c220e8bc74862901793d33","sourceId":"JournalEntry.p2CfgBp8vs3eOMBz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_li02unqb3w","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Bonus Objective B","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"5UhsYDOdABuA4ZYW","name":"BO-B: Scene A","content":"<div class=\"WordSection1\">\n<h1><span style=\"font-size:20.0pt;font-family:'Andada SC';mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Appendix 6: Tinder Moment (Bonus Objective B.)</span></h1>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\"><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Estimated Duration:</span> 60 minutes</p>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Cambria',serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:'ヒラギノ角ゴ Pro W3';mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:JA;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span></p>\n<div class=\"WordSection2\">\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Setting Description</h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:'Cambria',serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:'ヒラギノ角ゴ Pro W3';mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:JA;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\">On the second floor in a room towards the front of the house is the ghost of Renny Tinderhobb. The halfling child of Constable Hobb who died there two years ago.</p>\n<h3>Prerequisites</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">The players can arrive here from <strong>@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.5E3gCjSIdoaWrCh3]{Episode 2: Scene D} </strong><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">or they may do it after completing Story Objective B in <strong>@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.oQc7LUEa5Z3Jj7S5]{Episode 3: Scene C}</strong></span></p>\n<h3>Area Information</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">This area features:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Dimensions &amp; Terrain. </span></strong>The second floor of Coppertop Manor is made up of broken wooden floorboards which are <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">difficult terrain</em>.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>Lighting.</span> </strong>The manor is dimly lit from the moonlight outside. When observing from the outside a DC 18 Wisdom (perception) check will notice a flash of light from a window on the second floor.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">   <strong> </strong></span><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Traps and hazards.</span></strong> The main stairs and floors upstairs are treacherous. Periodically have the players attempt to succeed on a DC 15 Wisdom (perception) check to avoid rotted boards that break causing them to fall through for 1d6 bludgeoning damage.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">  </span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><strong><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span><span class=\"InlineSubhead\">Smells and sounds.</span></strong> The musty smell of moldy wall paper and rotted wood permeate the entire house. The sounds of creaking boards, and skittering feet can be heard throughout the manor. While inside the manor the crying of a child can be heard. DC 12 Wisdom (perception) check can determine that it is coming from the second floor.</p>\n<h3>Objectives</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">The players need to help the ghost of Renny Tinderhobb pass on.</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Scene A. Hole lot of scary</h2>\n</div>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">The players will need to get to the second floor to find the room where Denny Tinderhobb perished.</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt\">\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"BoxedText\">Stepping into this room the sky glooms overhead through a gaping hole in the roof, its remnants collapsed into a pile on the floor in the center of the room. Glancing about you see partially boarded windows looking out over a dead willow tree. Along the eastern wall sits a broken desk opposed by the remains of a bed on the western wall. The only door in the room is the one on the northern wall.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">A character with a Passive Perception of 12 or higher will notice the remains of tiny jacket under the rubble from the roof.</p>\n<h3>Creatures/NPCs</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">As the players begin to search the room they hear a mournful wail of the @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.06bw91XHkyRT7drF]{Ghost}(AL:NG) of Renny Tinderhobb. He manifests himself using his horrifying visage against all in the area who will need to succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or become <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">frightened</em>.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"BoldSerif\"><em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>Objectives/Goals.</em></span> </strong>Denny will attempt frighten the players until they can prove they are not a threat. He will then ask for the return of his favorite wooden kobold doll that went missing. It will be in a random debris pile somewhere in the house. <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">See scene @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.Sc8jn8Ht7NNQSbkx]{B. Piles of Excitement}. </strong>The doll will need to be returned to his grave to allow his ghost to pass on.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span><strong>What Does He Know?</strong></span> Renny will use his horrifying visage until the characters prove they are not the bad people. Once he is sure the player characters have good intentions he will appear as he was in life, a tiny halfling boy of 8 years and speak:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Renny used to sneak up here often to explore</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>He liked to play with his favorite wooden kobold doll but lost it somewhere in the house.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>He was looking for it in this room when the roof collapsed.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">  </span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>He can’t leave this room, but still wants to find his kobold doll.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>The bad people came about two months ago</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Their leader is a woman, who sounds sweet but is really mean.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Renny scared them away so they don’t bother him anymore.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:9.35pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>The bad people didn’t want to help find his doll, they only wanted to gather as many bodies as possible for “that guard [<em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">sic</em>]”.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>If the players have found the kobold doll, Renny will hover around the person with it and anxiously ask what they have in their pocket.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Renny will flit about excitedly once the doll is produced but he will not be able to rest and pass on until the doll is returned to his grave.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>Constable Hobb buried his son in the graveyard tended by Daeomer and either one can point out the location of the grave and give permission to inter the doll with Renny.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">  </span></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">   </span></span></span>A DC 20 Intelligence (investigation) check at the graveyard will discover Renny’s grave marker location without help.</p>\n<h3>Treasure &amp; Rewards</h3>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal\">Putting Renny to rest will earn the players the <strong>@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.9pasI5abhzmDRZEm]{Tinder Hearts}</strong><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> </strong>story award.</p>\n<hr />\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:normal\">See @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.journals.UJCAwvjiBXBd2sOC]{BO-B: Playing the Pillars} for more info.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"cg9GYXQMlimDSuHI":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.bKtCuoOUIN9LNr8s","hash":"de2248dd88d619b31fdc3035538eb9d8911d5856"},"cf":{"id":"temp_li02unqb3w","path":"The Mystery at Coppertop Manor#/CF_SEP/Bonus Objective B","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Sc8jn8Ht7NNQSbkx","name":"BO-B: Scene B","content":"<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #C4BC96 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:background2;mso-border-bottom-themeshade:191;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<h2>Scene B. Piles of Excitement</h2>\n</div>\n<p class=\"CoreBody\">Once inside the manor the players find dusty floors and piles of debris. Exploring the debris piles the players will find <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">trinkets</em>, <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">mundane items</strong>,<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">consumable items</em></strong>, and swarms of critters.</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt 4.0pt\">\n<p class=\"BoxedText\">The once polished marble checkered floor of the great foyer ends at a now rotted grand stair that rises the dusty floor to a broken balcony. To the left and right are a series of hallways and rooms. Piles of refuse and debris litter the rooms.</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Area Information</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">This area features:</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><strong><span class=\"InlineSubhead\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">    </span>Dimensions &amp; Terrain. </span></strong>The main foyer is 60 ft. wide by 55 ft. deep with a balcony hanging over the back 15 ft. of the hall. Other rooms on this floor are generally 20 ft. by 25 ft.</p>\n<h3>Creatures/NPCs</h3>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\">There are 6 piles of debris lying about the manor with 4 @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.PZ7ZY9XYevBdyevq]{Swarms of Rats}nestled<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"> </strong>throughout them.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpMiddle\"><strong><span class=\"BoldSerif\"><em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">Objectives/Goals.</em></span> </strong>Let the players explore as many or as few as they wish but be sure they find the @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.items.aey4ILGnFd8xyazl]{Wooden Kobold Doll} in at least one pile.</p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"> </p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid #F2F2F2 1.5pt;mso-border-themecolor:background1;mso-border-themeshade:242;padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\">\n<p class=\"SidebarHeading\">Adjusting the Scene<span class=\"MsoCommentReference\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:'MS Mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-fareast-language:EN-US\"> </span></span></p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBody\">Here are some suggestions for adjusting this scene, according to your group.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Very Weak: </span>Remove three <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">swarms of rats</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span class=\"BoldSerif\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Weak: </span>Remove one <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">swarm of rats</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Strong: </span>Add four <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">swarms of rats</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBulletedCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left:.1in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.1in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;background:#EEECE1;mso-background-themecolor:background2\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#9b3737\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">  </span></span></span><span class=\"BoldSerif\">Very Strong: </span>Add four @Compendium[pla01-tmacm.actors.LEtX1Talo8mssdJl]{Swarms of Beetles}.</p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpFirst\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\"> </em></strong></p>\n<p class=\"CoreBodyCxSpLast\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\">Treasure.</em></strong> Roll on the debris pile chart for each pile.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBody\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Debris Piles.</strong> Roll [[/gmr 1d4]] times on this chart when searching a debris pile. One of each item per pile may be found, ignore duplicates and reroll. Roll a [[/r 1d4]] to determine which pile list and a [[/r 1d20]] for line item.</p>\n<p class=\"SidebarBody\"> </p>\n<table style=\"width:72.5775%;height:369.6px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:33.6px\">\n<th style=\"width:5.25088%;height:33.6px\">[[/r 1d20]]</th>\n<th style=\"width:20.4201%;height:33.6px\">@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.rolltables.lNSBzU8LjRfHP1G2]{Debris Pile 1}</th>\n<th style=\"width:27.5379%;height:33.6px\">@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.rolltables.6dbdSnaijbkbOwKh]{Debris Pile 2}</th>\n<th style=\"width:23.4539%;height:33.6px\">@Compendium[pla01-tmacm.rollt